            h2 School
            p Academics and coursework are a large part of the life of an Andover student, comprising both the school day and an average of 4 hours outside of the classroom, with 115 students spending 6 hours outside of the classroom. On top of coursework, many students also participate in additional extracurricular activities. Nearly 64% of respondents reported that part of the reason they participate in extracurricular activities is to increase the chances of admission to a selective college. When looking at college admissions, Andover students are nearly split as to whether attending Andover would increase their chances of admission to a selective college, with 50.9% reporting that it would help their chances positively and 42.3% reporting that it would negatively impact their chances. 
