            h2 Wellness
            p Addressing student wellness has been at the forefront of Andover’s mission to help students stay balanced. 78.65% of students generally consider themselves happy at Andover, but only 63.09% of students think Andover students are happy. The largest percentage of students (38.52%) find their support system in their friends, with support systems including faculty and Sykes staff in addition to friends coming in a close second (33.40%). Less than half of the student body has visited Graham House or Sykes Wellness Center to see a counselor. On campus, 166 students have been diagnosed with depression and 187 students have been diagnosed with anxiety.
