            h2 Drugs
            p Students of the Upper socioeconomic class have the highest percentages in ever consuming alcohol, tobacco products, using “juuls,” hallucinogens or hard drugs, pharmaceutical or “study” drugs, or purchasing a fake ID. The Lower socioeconomic class has the highest percentages in using marijuana. Out of all Andover students, 21.61% have attended a school-sponsored event under the influence of drugs or alcohol, while 11.57% have used drugs or alcohol during an academic school day.
